Essential Reference Works:

 The FORTH Programmer's Handbook - Edward Conklin & Elizabeth Rather

 The Linux Programming Interface - Michael Kerrisk

 Beginning Linux Programming - Neil Matthew & Richard Stones

 Computer Systems: A Programmer's Perspective, 3rd Edition - Randal Bryant & David O'Hallaron

 Elementary Functions: Algorithms and Implementation - Jean-Michel Muller

 Modern Computer Arithmetic - Richard Brent & Paul Zimmermann

 AMD64 Programming Guides

 32/64-Bit 80x86 Assembly Language Architecture - James Leiterman

 x86-64 Assembly Language Programming with Ubuntu - Ed Jorgensen

 Introduction to 64 Bit Intel Assembly Language Programming for Linux - Ray Seyfarth


Essential Programs for Development:

 yasm, gcc, udis86, ddd, gnome-terminal


Essential Utilities:

 meld, recoll, xxd, nasm, ndisasm, objdump


Best Programming Editors:

 sublime-text, jedit, vim, gedit


Other References:

 Computer Methods for Mathematical Computations - George E. Forsythe, Michael A. Malcolm, and Cleve B. Moler

 On the Normalization Requirement of Divisor in Divide-and-Correct Methods - E.V. Krishnamurthy & Salil Nandi - Communications of the ACM, Volume 10, Number 12, December 1967

 A Multiple-Precision Division Algorithm - Charles J. Mifsud - Communications of the ACM, Volume 13, Number 11, November 1970

 Computation of Pi Using Arithmetic-Geometric Mean - Eugene Salamin - Mathematics of Computation, Volume 30, Number 135, July 1976

